<subSubSection id="C33E44D6FFB0FFF4809029F633EA9E71" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="40" pageId="8" pageNumber="39" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9B175DFFB0FFF4809029F633EA9E71" blockId="8.[136,1452,1843,2086]" lastBlockId="9.[136,1452,158,293]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="40" pageId="8" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis id="B950CB4FFFB0FFF5809029F6367298EC" bold="true" box="[189,356,1951,1977]" pageId="8" pageNumber="39">Comments:—</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C246CDEFFB0FFF582AE29C935E298EF" box="[643,756,1952,1978]" class="Myxomycetes" family="Physaraceae" genus="Physarum" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Physarales" pageId="8" pageNumber="39" phylum="Mycetozoa" rank="species" species="vernum">P. vernum</taxonomicName>
but this usually has lighter spores that are evenly light brown in colour in transmitted light, plasmodiocarps and a rather reddish-brown mass of spores under magnification (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB56AACFFB0FFF5854929AA37D39757" author="Kuhnt, A." pageId="8" pageNumber="39" pagination="39 - 64" refId="ref5874" refString="Kuhnt, A. (2014) Bemerkenswerte, Schleimpilze (Amoebozoa, Myxomycetes) aus Deutschland: Neu- und Wiederfunde seltener Arten. Berichte der Bayerischen Botanischen Gesellschaft 84: 39 - 64." type="journal article" year="2014">Kuhnt 2014</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB56AACFFB0FFF580FB298E36AE9757" author="Poulain, M. &amp; Meyer, M. &amp; Bozonnet, J." box="[214,440,2023,2050]" pageId="8" pageNumber="39" pagination="406" refId="ref6272" refString="Poulain, M., Meyer, M. &amp; Bozonnet, J. (2011) Les Myxomycetes. Federation Mycologique et Botanique Dauphine-Savoie. Sevrier Pl 215: 406." type="journal article" year="2011">
Poulain 
<emphasis id="B950CB4FFFB0FFF5811F298136749754" box="[306,354,2023,2049]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="39">et al</emphasis>
. (2011)
</bibRefCitation>
separated this taxon from 
<taxonomicName id="4C246CDEFFB0FFF582F12981345C9754" box="[732,842,2024,2049]" class="Myxomycetes" family="Physaraceae" genus="Physarum" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Physarales" pageId="8" pageNumber="39" phylum="Mycetozoa" rank="species" species="vernum">
<emphasis id="B950CB4FFFB0FFF582F12981345C9754" box="[732,842,2024,2049]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="39">P. vernum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by greyish colour of the peridium covered by scattered lime flakes, the darker spore mass, a well developed badhamioid capillitium with large, angular nodes densely stuffed with granules (0.5–2 μm in diam.) which are not very distinct in outline and the appearance of the spores which are darker but have a paler side and show a more regular ornamentation of warts (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB56AACFFB1FFF484352EAB323F9F89" author="Novozhilov, Y. K. &amp; Schnittler, M. &amp; Erastova, D. A. &amp; Okun, M. V. &amp; Schepin, O. N. &amp; Heinrich, E." box="[1048,1321,194,221]" pageId="9" pageNumber="40" pagination="109 - 130" refId="ref6150" refString="Novozhilov, Y. K., Schnittler, M., Erastova, D. A., Okun, M. V., Schepin, O. N. &amp; Heinrich, E. (2013) Diversity of nivicolous myxomycetes of the Teberda State Biosphere Reserve (Northwestern Caucasus, Russia). Fungal Diversity 59: 109 - 130. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 13225 - 012 - 0199 - 0" type="journal article" year="2013">
Novozhilov 
<emphasis id="B950CB4FFFB1FFF484852EAA33CA9F89" box="[1192,1244,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="40">et al</emphasis>
. 2013
</bibRefCitation>
). The main features are the occurrence in the nivicolous environment, more rounded sporocarps in outline, absence of extensive plasmodiocarps, very dark spore mass under the microscope and spores which are lighter on one side.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
